Media personality and Chief Executive Officer of EbonyLife Studios, Mo Abudu, on Saturday celebrated being a grandmother for the second time. The excited 57-year-old took to her Instagram page to share a picture of herself and her two grandsons as she appreciated God for the latest addition. She also added that seeing her parents turn great grandparents was a ‘priceless joy’. The media mogul further congratulated her daughter and the new mother, Temidayo, and her son-in-law, Adebola on the birth of their son. In 2019, Temidayo Abudu married Adebola Makanjuola in California, United States. They welcomed their first son, Adetunji, fondly called TJ, in February 2020. Celebrating the birth of TJ’s baby brother, Mo Abudu wrote, “Good morning beautiful people. All glory to God, two weeks ago, I became a grandmother for the second time. “TJ now has a baby brother, Ireoluwa. It’s an amazing feeling, being grandmother to two amazing boys. “Seeing my dear mum now 80 and grandpa Abudu 95 now great grandparents for the second time gives our families priceless joy. “My darling Temidee and Adebola, congratulations. I pray God keeps you all enveloped in his arms now and always. “To the entire family, grandmas, grandpas, aunties and uncles, we praise God for the blessing to our family.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com